node.text:
To all athletes, teams, and supporters of the #OlympicGames2020: Keep your WILL – the (Olympic) flame is still burning strong!!! 🔥🔥 After careful consideration I struggle with myself to pass on a few personal words. As the IOC Boxing Task Force Champion🥊, I support boxers on their way to probably their greatest sport challenge in life: The opportunity to participate in the Olympic Games. 
Since #covid19 crossed all of our paths, the road to even start the games again, has become longer. One more year of training, sweat and pain! 💪🏼💪🏼
Never turn your back on your challenge…! What do you do to keep your goal fresh in your mind?🏆 #olympicgames2020 #covid19 #stayhome #weareinthistogether

node.text: September 25, 1999 is a special day for me. That was the evening I won my first international title as a professional. I became European Champion and got recognized almost "overnight" - especially in Germany. I owe that mainly to my opponent, Axel Schulz. “The People’s Champion” a people’s darling. We fought in his home country, Germany, in the “Kölnarena”. I realized early that evening that I would perform well and win. I was absolutely obsessed with this fight, focused on winning. I was very familiar with Axel's boxing style. I liked it. Good for me, less for him. After 8 rounds the fight was decided by TKO. The beginning of my great journey. Still today, I am grateful for this evening, this experience, this opponent, an incredible sportsman. After 20 years we returned to the place where it all happened and started... We are both in our second careers now and we are happy. Isn’t this the best outcome? Being happy with what you achieved and also be happy in the Here and Now.

node.text:
Congratulations to England for a great game played!

It didn't go in the direction I wanted, but that's sports. I’ve been on the losing side in my sport, as you all know, especially you, English fans. 

It's not about losing, it's about giving it all and coming back even stronger, we all love comebacks, don't we?!

I also am very proud of the Ukrainian team, we need to hold our heads up high, as we went far into this tournament, showing, we can compete. 🙏

I have no doubt, we can go even further. Watch us. 🤝

Until next time friends, thanks to y’all fans! 

As a professional athlete, I never take for granted, how important y’all are. Keep rooting and one day, maybe I will even hear you cheer my name, once again.

#UEFAEURO2020 🇺🇦vs🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿
